<p><placeName>Pleasant Fountain</placeName> <date when="1817-12-18">Decr. 18th 1817</date></p>
<p>Dear Sir you will be so good as to pay to <persName>Mr Wm Harrison</persName> forty 
dollars and forty Cents the amount of your and your <persName>farther</persName>s account
as he had not the mony when we settled and I owe <persName>Mr. Harrison</persName> and
he is a going a way your compliance will much oblige</p>

<p><persName>Mr. S. F. Austin</persName>      </p>

<p><persName>A. Miller</persName></p>

<p>N. B. <persName>Mr Harrison</persName> has our settlement which you Can see what the
Ballance is due me.</p>

<p><persName>A. M.</persName></p>

<p>Recd the within in full <date when="1817-12-19">Decb. 19 1817</date></p>

<p><persName>Black Smith</persName> a/c <date n="xx-xx-1816">1816</date>______________   6. 50

do              <date n="xx-xx-1817">1817</date>______________   8. 50
					      _______
						15. 00
order on <persName>S Perry and Co</persName>____________ 25. 40
						_______
					     $40. 40</p>
<p><persName>Wm. Habbison</persName></p>


